# 02-Frontend: Architecture & Interior Design UI

This rule applies to all frontend code in `client/src/`. It prioritizes performance, accessibility, and a premium, clean design.

## 1. Design System & Styling
- **Theme**: Premium architectural aesthetic. Use the "Assistant" font family.
- **Components**: Use ONLY `client/src/components/ui/` for primitive elements. Avoid raw HTML tags for styled elements.
- **Tailwind 3**: Use utility classes for all styling. Refer to `client/tailwind.config.js` for custom colors and spacing.
- **RTL Support**: Default to Hebrew layout (`dir="rtl"`). Ensure text alignment (`text-right`), margins (`ml` instead of `mr`), and padding are handled correctly for RTL.
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach. Verify all layouts on mobile (mobile-vid-hero) and desktop.

## 2. React 18 & Performance
- **React 18**: Use modern hooks and patterns. Ensure `main.tsx` uses `createRoot`.
- **Bundle Optimization**: Use `React.lazy()` for page-level components to reduce the initial bundle size.
- **Data Fetching**: Use TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) for cacheable API data. Query keys live in `client/src/constants/queryKeys.ts`. Use Axios services from `client/src/services/` with proper error handling and loading states.
- **Contexts**: Use contexts in `client/src/contexts/` for global state (Auth, Categories, Projects, Screen). Projects and Categories contexts wrap `useQuery` for shared cached data.

## 3. Motion & Animation
- **Motion Package**: Use `motion` primitives. Favor smooth, subtle architectural reveals (ease-in-out).
- **Project Displays**: Ensure high-quality image handling with `react-zoom-pan-pinch` for project details.

## 4. Forms & Validation
- **React Hook Form**: Always use `react-hook-form` for all client-side forms.
- **Zod Validation**: Use schemas from `@shirans/shared` to validate forms via `@hookform/resolvers/zod`.
- **Loading States**: Every async action MUST show a `Loader`, `Skeleton`, or `Spinner` from `client/src/components/Loader/`.

## 5. Directory Structure & Naming
- **Components**: Follow the structure in `client/src/components/` (Admin, Auth, Layout, Navbar, etc.).
- **Pages**: Define page components in `client/src/pages/`. Keep pages thin — orchestrate components and hooks only.
- **Assets**: Store SVGs in `client/src/assets/`.

## 6. Separation of Concerns (MANDATORY)

Always separate client code into the right layer:

- **Hooks** (`client/src/hooks/`): Reusable logic (data fetching, form state, API calls). Extract when logic is shared or complex.
- **Components** (`client/src/components/`): Reusable UI. Extract subcomponents to separate files when they grow (>50 lines or clearly reusable).
- **Pages** (`client/src/pages/`): Thin orchestrators. Compose components + hooks. No business logic inline.
- **Constants/Options**: Extract option arrays, config objects to `constants.ts` or `options.ts` within the feature folder (e.g. `components/Calculator/constants.ts`).
- **Utils**: Pure functions go in `client/src/utils/` or a local `utils.ts` in the feature folder.

**Example**: A form with options, a Select subcomponent, and submit logic → `CalculatorForm.tsx` (component) + `calculatorOptions.ts` (constants) + `useCalculatorSubmit` (hook) + `Select.tsx` (extracted component if reused).

## 7. Verification Checklist
- [ ] Is it RTL compatible (Hebrew alignment)?
- [ ] Does it use the UI component library in `client/src/components/ui/`?
- [ ] Are animations smooth and accessible?
- [ ] Is form validation synced with `@shirans/shared`?
- [ ] Tested on both mobile and desktop views?
